  subhead="You post a twelve-second reel filmed from a drone — a high-reach excavator systematically demolishing a five-storey former council office building in Cowley. The long boom reaches across the exclusion zone, the concrete pulveriser bites into the reinforced concrete parapet wall, rubble cascades down the face of the building into the catch net, and dust suppression creates a mist around the demolition zone. Two hundred and forty likes, ninety-one shares. A property investor in Headington messages: 'Impressive work — I have just bought a former care home in Headington. 3 storeys, brick construction, about 900 sqm. Need it demolished for residential development. Asbestos report done — some ACMs in the boiler room. Would need the whole site cleared and levelled. Can you give me a ballpark?' You are on site. Without AI Messenger, the message waits until the portakabin. With it, the AI asks about the basement (if any), whether the boundary walls are retained, and the anticipated development start date. The investor confirms no basement, retain the front boundary wall, and development starts in twelve weeks. Your lead is captured — former care home, Headington, 3 storeys, 900 sqm, brick, ACMs in boiler room, residential development, boundary wall retention, twelve-week start."
